th 36.76% P99 increase\n   - `shippingservice-1` and `currencyservice-1` also show notable latency increases\n\n3. **Database Impact**: TiDB-TiKV component shows I/O utilization issues, which could be contributing to the overall system performance degradation.\n\nThe memory pressure on node `aiops-k8s-08` appears to be the root cause, as it's hosting critical services and the memory availability reduction is substantial enough to impact overall system performance.\n\n--- Trace Agent Findings ---\nBased on the trace data analysis, I can now provide a detailed analysis of the abnormal event. Let me examine the latency patterns and error propagation to identify the root cause.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"error_ratio\",\n    \"checkoutservice->shippingservice\",\n    \"frontend->checkoutservice\",\n    \"frontend->adservice\",\n    \"cartservice->redis\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"ShippingService/ShipOrder latency increased from 217ms to 1279ms (5.9x) and from 237ms to 1203ms (5.1x), indicating severe performance degradation\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Checkout service self-calls show massive latency increases: ShipOrder from 13.9s to 72.9s (5.2x), EmptyCart from 18.2s to 83s (4.6x), GetCart from 8.5s to 35.9s (4.2x)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Multiple frontend instances show 'context deadline exceeded' errors (status code 4) when calling AdService/GetAds, indicating timeout failures\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Redis operations show significant latency increases: HMSET from 1.6s to 33.9s (20.5x) and HGET from 1.6s to 7.4s (4.8x), suggesting database performance issues\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Root Cause Analysis Summary:\n\nThe primary root cause appears to be a **cascading failure** starting from the **shippingservice** and **redis** components:\n\n1. **Initial Trigger**: Redis performance degradation (20.5x latency increase) affecting cartservice operations\n2. **Primary Impact**: Shipping service experiencing 5-6x latency increases, causing checkout operations to timeout\n3. **Cascading Effect**: Checkout service self-calls show massive latency increases (4-5x), indicating retries and timeouts\n4. **Propagation**: Frontend services experience \"context deadline exceeded\" errors when calling downstream services\n\nThe most severe performance degradation is observed in Redis operations and shipping service calls, suggesting these are the root cause components that triggered the cascading failure across the system during the specified time window.\n\n--- Previous Consensus Decision ---\nNo consensus yet", "metric_analysis_findings": "See Log Findings for Full Context", "trace_analysis_findings": "See Log Findings for Full Context", "consensus_decision": "AGREED", "current_hypothesis": "adservice-0 is the root cause due to Byteman agent injection causing performance degradation (AdService--gc-1749841811 rule execution and GC helper triggering)"}
